HEADWORD: Tymbal
<hw>Tym"bal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>timbale</ets>, Sp. <ets>timbal</ets>; cf. <ets>atabal</ets>;
probably of Arabic origin. Cf. <er>Atabal</er>, <er>Timbrel</er>.]</ety>
<def>A kind of kettledrum.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>timbal</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>tymbal's</qex> sound were better than my voice.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tymp</ent>⟦br⟧
